<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Delayed network provisioning>
We are investigating delayed network provisioning for newly launched instances in a single Availability Zone in the US-EAST-1 Region.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Increased provisioning times>
We are investigating increased provisioning times for load balancers in the US-EAST-1 Region. Registration of back-end instances and connectivity to existing instances are not affected.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Informational message: Delays in starting clusters>
We are investigating delays in starting Amazon EMR clusters in the US-EAST-1 Region. Existing clusters are not impacted.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Delayed network provisioning>
Between 5:27 AM and 8:17 AM PDT we experienced delayed network provisioning for newly launched instances in a single Availability Zone in the US-EAST-1 Region. The issue have been resolved and the service is operating normally.

<http://status.aws.amazon.com/|Service is operating normally: [RESOLVED] Delays in starting clusters>
Between 7:00 AM and 8:15 AM PDT we experienced delays in starting Amazon EMR clusters in the US-EAST-1 Region. Existing clusters were not impacted. The issue has been resolved and the service is operating normally.
